cs.SY, cs.MA, cs.NE, cs.SI, cs.DC 

The paper deals with the detection and isolation of failures in a network of linear agents, which falls under the category of systems and control (cs.SY). The use of sensor placement and observation of jump discontinuities in the network output also suggests a possible category of multi-agent systems (cs.MA). The paper also discusses the use of computer experiments, which could fall under the category of neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) or social and information networks (cs.SI). Finally, the paper deals with the detection and isolation of link failures, which could fall under the category of distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC).
